    "The compression of each spatial domain H x W is achieved through global average pooling, which yields a value output.",
    "The final output of the squeeze stage is a vector of size 1 x 1 x C. More specifically, the calculation of the cth element of the squeeze output, denoted as S q, is expressed as follows:S q (N O, Z) = 1 H × W H i=1 W j=1 D 0 (N O, i, j, Z)(3)where, H x W represents the dimension of the output (Do) of the residual block.",
    "The squeeze output S q is derived from this output.",
    "Furthermore, N O and Z correspond to the batch size and the number of feature maps, respectively.",
    "The excitation stage involves capturing interdependencies among channels via a gate mechanism that comprises two nonlinear fully connected layers."
